{
  "stem": "27340.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he was in fact-- most of his time was in Eastern-- in fact, extensively in Eastern Europe, particularly on the Russian front.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he served there as an expert in logistics and transportation, because such was the nature of my-- the business that my grandfather had founded, a business of forwarding agents, as it were.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That means that they-- they transported goods from one place to another to their specific destinations.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They had-- the headquarters of the company was in Breslau and, oddly enough, within the old original ghetto.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But that was just a coincidence I should imagine certainly.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they had a branch in Szczecin, which was at the mouth of the Odra into the Baltic Sea.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then they had an agency in Chicago, from where they imported a tremendous amount of meat into Germany, into-- into Breslau via ships, of course, in those days.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And Breslau was a major city for distribution.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It was the gateway, if you like, to Eastern Europe.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It was a city of about half a million inhabitants and played a major part both as a traffic center, you can call it that, mainly rail, of course.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Roads in those days were not quite as-- as functional as they are today.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And they distributed goods that had been bought by other organizations to Eastern Europe, certainly to Prague, to Poland, and as far perhaps as the Ukraine and White Russia.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, indeed.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My grandfather's name was Samuel.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my father's name was Franz.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My mother was called Margereta.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I was named Stefan.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the emphasis there is put on the first letter S, because it was intended.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My parents intended this, my grandparents, that I would ultimately follow them into the business.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
